  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "In-House Driver (Mercedes Van)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Safely operate company vehicles to deliver and collect goods, documents or materials while supporting warehouse and logistics tasks to ensure smooth operations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive company vehicles safely to deliver and collect goods, documents or materials as assigned</li><li>Plan and follow efficient delivery routes to ensure timely transport</li><li>Load and unload goods carefully, handling cartons up to 5KG to prevent damage</li><li>Maintain accurate logs of daily driving activities including mileage, fuel usage and delivery records</li><li>Comply with all road safety regulations and company policies during driving duties</li><li>Perform basic vehicle checks on oil, water, tires and lights, and report any issues promptly</li><li>Arrange scheduled vehicle servicing and repairs to maintain roadworthiness</li><li>Keep vehicle clean inside and out to ensure a professional appearance and safety</li><li>Assist other departments with ad hoc warehouse and logistics tasks as needed</li><li>Handle goods with care and ensure all related documentation is accurate and complete</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Possess a valid local driving license (e.g., Class 3/3A)</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>1–2 years of driving experience</li><li>Experience in warehouse operations</li><li>Ability to lift and move goods weighing up to 5KG per carton</li><li>Good knowledge of local roads and traffic regulations</li><li>Basic literacy and numeracy skills for managing inventory and delivery records</li><li>Punctual, responsible, and able to work independently and collaboratively within a team</li></ul>",
